devdoc.details: SLARegistry is a contract for handling creation of service level agreements and keeping track of the created agreements

SLACount().details: public view function that returns the total amount of service level agreements

allSLAs().details: public view function that returns all the service level agreements

params._messengerAddress: the address of the chainlink messenger contract

createSLA(address,address,address,bytes3.details: public function for creating service level agreements

params._SLONames: Array of the names of the service level objectives in bytes32
params._SLOs: Array of service level objective contract addressess
params._compensationAmount: Uint of the amount of DSLA to compensate on service level objective breach
params._dsla: Address of the DSLA token contract
params._ipfsHash: String with the ipfs hash that contains extra information about the service level agreement
params._owner: Address of the owner of the service level agreement
params._poolSize: uint the size of the compensation pool the creator will initialize the contract with
params._sliInterval: uint the interval in seconds between requesting a new SLI
params._stake: Uint of the amount required to stake when signing the service level agreement

paginatedSLAs(uint256,uint256).details: external view function that returns the service level agreements for a certain range in the array

params._end: the index of the end position in the array
params._start: the index of the start position in the array

subscribedSLAs(address).details: public view function that returns the service level agreements the user is subscribed to

subscriptionCount(address).details: public view function that returns the amount of SLA's the user is subscribed to

userSLACount(address).details: public view function that returns the amount of service level agreements the given user is the owner of

params._user: Address of the user for which to return the amount of service level agreements

userSLAs(address).details: public view function that returns the service level agreements that the given user is the owner of

params._user: Address of the user for which to return the service level agreements
